review_blob: Light and hoppy with a nice malt balance. Lots of citrus in the hops. Clean finish and very easy to drink.
Petty good for an Amber ale. Lots of floral hop aroma. Flavor is not bad, though a bit mild for my usual taste preferences. Finish is bitter, but overall its a fairly well balanced ale.
A great summer beer. Light, refreshing and tasty. Just enough hope for a bit of flavor and bittering, but very well balanced. It wont blow your sock off, but not every good beer will.

Pours black with really no head. Aroma is raisin and alcohol. A bit thick, but not sticky sweet with little carbonation. Flavor is very nice, but boozy. Some dark roast, a bit of dried fruit and a bitter finish make for a fairly well balance, if a bit hot beer.

On tap at hearthstone pub. Pours opaque dark brown, nearly black with a small tan head. Flavor and aroma are coffee, cocoa and booze. Almost tasted oak aged to me, even though its not. A very fine stout.
beer_name: Ballast Point Sea Monster Imperial Stout

review_blob: Completely one dimensional beer. Flavor is as bitter as it gets with no sweetness to offset. Finish is, surprise, bitter. I always try to support our local brewers, but cant say that I enjoyed this.
Pours very pale an clear with lots of tiny bubbles. Aroma is spicy. Mouth feel is light with a lot of carbonation. Flavor is reminiscent of a Saison with nice spice and a touch of lemon. Very good.

Clear amber with a small head. Aroma is very champagne like. Medium in body with good carbonation. Flavor is very good with nice fruity overtones and a bit of alcohol, though not as much as the abv would predict. Very nice.
beer_name: New Holland Black Tulip Trippel Ale

review_blob: As a non coffee drinker, I may not be the right person to rate this beer. Aroma is combination of coffee and some caramel. The flavor is bitter and very strong of coffee. There is also some lemony tartness present, but I cant get past all the coffee.

Pours clear copper with a medium head. Aroma is nothing to write home about. A bit of grass and caramel. Medium in body with good carbonation. Flavor is surprisingly not all that happy. Sweet malt flavors are up front with a bitter end. Despite the lack of complexity, I actually quite enjoyed this.

Pours a nice brown with a medium head. Pretty thick in body with enough carbonation to prevent stickiness. Flavor is a bit on the sweet side, but expected for the style. Caramel is the way out front. Finish is sweet, but not cloyingly so. A good dopplebock.

Pours cloudy straw yellow with a medium head. Nose is very citrus with lemon and some grass. Fairly thin in body with lots of carbonation. Flavor has a lot of lemon and a lot of barnyard funk. Not bad but missing the fruity complexity of the best sessions. Finish is slightly bitter.

Absolutely fantastic Saison. Pours cloudy gold with a small head. Aroma is fruity with a hint of horse blanket. Flavor is sweet, but well balanced with a lot of fruit (apple) up front and just a hint of hop.

Very dark opaque pour with a small brown head. A bit thick in body and lightly carbonated. Flavor is coffee, caramel and a bit of prune. A nice hop bite finishes this one nicely. Oh so dark and oh so good.

Pours dark but translucent brown with a very small head. Aroma is a bit off with some cardboard. Medium to thick in body with light carbonation. LucKily the off aroma is not present in the flavor. Alcohol is surprisingly up front Ib the flavor profile, malty sweetness, a bit of hop bite and a hint of cherry round this one out.
Not a bad IPA, but I did not taste much of the oak aging, and so was disappointed. Pretty much just tasted like Hatter.
beer_name: New Holland Oak Aged Hatter IPA

review_blob: Pours opaque dark chocolate with a small tan head. Aroma is vanilla, chocolate and a bit of oak. Pretty thick in body, but not sticky. Flavor is complex and delicious. Vanilla is in the forefront, but there are also nice roasted chocolate and coffee overtones. In the background are oak, alcohol, char and a bit of a hop bite. This is really my kind of beer.

On tap at Waxys. Dark amber with a small head. Thick and a bit sticky with good carbonation. Aroma is floral and malt. Flavor is a good balance of hop bitterness and sweet malt. Lots of nice hop citrus and grassy flavors. Very good, but I had no idea the abv was as high as it is while drinking this.
Pours yellow with a medium head. Aroma is mostly rosemary with a hint of spice. Flavor is herby and interesting. Finish is clean. Im not sure I love this, but its definitely different.
beer_name: Dogfish Head / Victory / Stone Saison du BUFF

review_blob: From a bottle, pours gold with a bit of a haze. Aroma is lemongrass. Flavor is sweet with a lot of hop presence. Lemon and citrus with a serious hop bitterness. Finish is very bitter.

Pours gold with a smallish head of white bubbles. Aroma kind of smells like an apple wine. I bit thick in mouth feel, but lots of bubbles. Flavor is very boozy with apple undertones and a sweetness up front. After taste is actually really good with a lingering apple presence. I like it.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: I wasnt very impressed with this, but it wasnt terrible either. pours a nice copper color with a medium head. The body is quote thin, but has good carbonation. Flavor is on the light side with a bit of a metallic after taste. Not a great fest, but then again its not really a great style to start with

This beer is the bomb. A very dark pour with a small tan head. Aroma is dark roast. A bit thick in mouth feel, but not cloying with good carbonation. Flavor is perfectly balanced with dark roasted chocolate and coffee notes, a good hop bit and nice alcohol burn.

Pours good with a nice head. Aroma is your standard Belgian ale with lots of fruity overtones. Thin to medium in body with lovely carbonation. Flavor is nicely balanced with sweet fruit and a good alcohol presence.
beer_name: New England 668 Neighbor of the Beast

review_blob: Had on tap. Pour is golden with a nice head. Aroma appeared to be mostly citrus, but was overpowered by other smells in the establishment. Light in body with lots of carbonation. Flavor is very happy, but not overly bitter. Floral and citrus dominate with a bit of malt sweetness, but not quite enough to balance perfectly.
Black as night with a tan head. Thick in body with just enough carbonation to prevent stickiness, Flavor is fantastic with tons of dark roasted malty and a touch of sour.
On tap. Golden with a small head. Aroma is mostly pine with some honey. Medium in body with good carbonation. Flavor is a bit bitter at first but gradually changes to a sweet malt.
Pours dark brown with a small head. Aroma is banana. A bit thick in body with light carbonation. Flavor is not as banana as the nose with some nice nutty flavors
I feel like I[m rating a different beer than the others. This tasted nothing like a triple. There was far too much hops presence. Not at all a good example, but I guess its OK for what it is.
Pours reddish amber with a small head. Nose is all malt. A bit sticky but well carbonated. Flavor is delicious and the finish is sweet. Way to easy to drink for the ABV, but oh so very yummy.
Tastes like a Belgian write, but but nearly as good as the best of the style. Even blue moon has it easily bested.
Dark amber with a nice head. Aroma is woody and sweet. Medium in body with good carbonation. Flavor is a bit bitter for my taste, but there is a good amount of malty sweetness.

From a can. Pours clear brass with a nice head. Aroma is pine citrus and alcohol. Not at all sticky with lots of carbonation. Flavor is pine, caramel and citrus. Hop bite is balanced nicely by the sweet malt. Alcohol is not overbearing especially considering the ABV. A very good DIPA.

Pours dark amber with a good head. Aroma is a mixture of bread and sweet malt. Medium in body with good carbonation. Flavor is on the sweet side with some biscuit and a touch of fruit, maybe apricot. Not bad, but not one of my favorites.

Aroma is sweet with banana clove and some alcohol. Medium in body with good carbonation. Flavor follows the nose with a bit more alcohol presence. A very good beer, but not as as some others of the same style.

Pours gold as the sun with a nice head. Aroma is mostly pine with a bit of malt.
Light to medium in body with good carbonation..
Flavor is more complex than the nose would indicate with a lot of fruity sweetness behind a hop bite. 
Finish is smooth.

Pours dark orangeish brown with a good head.
Medium in body and well carbonated.
Dark fruit abounds in the flavor along with a nice alcohol bite. 
This was a delicious beer that I look forward to having again.

Pours black with a small brown head. Aroma is a rich of coffee with sweet malt. Thin in body with just enough carbonation. Flavor is mild but not bad, some dark roast and just a rich of hop bitterness.

On tap at Wood N Tap southington Ct. Pours cloudy gold work a good sized head. Aroma is citrus and a bit of malt. Medium in body with good carbonation. Flavor is very hoppy with lots of citrus a touch of pine and just enough malt for balance. A pretty strong alcohol burn follows.
beer_name: Dogfish Head Hellhound On My Ale

review_blob: Pours clear golden with a nice white head. The aroma of flowers and fruit are promising. A bit thin in body, but nice carbonation. Flavor consists of orchard fruit a bit of must, and an off soapy characteristic that unfortunately rubbed this for me. I really wanted to like it, but ended up putting half the bottle down the drain.

Pours clear yellow with a small head. Aroma is not really pleasant with a dish soap undertone. Thin in body with good carbonation. Flavor is very mild and barely present. The good news is the soapy smell does not carry through in the flavor.

Pours cloudy yellow with a big head. Aroma is typical with bread like yeast and banana. Medium in body with good carbonation. Flavor is good. if a bit mild with banana, bread and a touch of clove. The best of the Konig Ludwig line.

Pours clear brown with a touch of red. Aroma is mostly molasses. A bit sticky in body with not quite enough carbonation. Flavor is very sweet with lots of molasses and a hint of alcohol. Not very exciting.
Pours black with a small head.Aroma is roasted malt with a bit of coffee. Thin in body, maybe a bit too thin for a stout. Flavor is light but pleasant. Good for a hot summers day in salzburg
Pours cloudy brown with a big head. Aroma is molasses and yeast. A bit thick with good carbonation. Flavor is sweet and one dimensional.
Hazy yellow with a giant head.Aroma is mostly banana with a but of yeast. Medium in body with lots of carbonation. Smooth flavor with banana, bread and a touch of clove. Very good.
Dark gold with a medium head. Aroma is mostly malt and alcohol. Medium in body with good carbonation. Flavor is a bit sweet with a bit of hops to balance.
beer_name: Alsacienne du Gambrinus - LAlsace de toujours

review_blob: Pours hazy gold with a big head.Aroma is banana and must.Thin in body with good carbonation. Flavor is mild with banana and a hint of clove.
Golden in color with a medium head. Aroma is citrus and a hint of pine. Thin in body with good carbonation. Flavor is subtle, but quite good with citrus, malt sweetness and a but of a hop bite.

Pours dark brown with a small head. Aroma is caramel, fig and alcohol. Thick and a bit sticky. Flavor is full and complex with fig, oak, and alcohol being dominant. Finish is sweet, but not cloying. Excellent.
